The CLI runs. The `quote` function currently returns `undefined` (it's a stub), so we get `[null]`. Once the implementation is filled in through the TDD cycle, the CLI will return proper values.

The CLI at `src/cli.ts`:
- Reads JSON from stdin (supports a single object or an array of steps)
- Processes each step by dispatching on the `action` field (currently supports `"quote"`)
- Writes a JSON array of results to stdout
- On error, writes the message to stderr and exits with code 1

You can run it with `npx tsx src/cli.ts` or `echo '<json>' | npx tsx src/cli.ts`.
